// Deployment-runtime axis service contract. Status: v1 (frozen — rat/1.3; two divergent references: local-process + k8s-dryrun).
//
// A `kind: deployment-runtime` plugin (local-process, docker, podman, k8s,
// nomad, lambda, fargate) is WHERE PLUGINS RUN. Distinct from `runtime` (where
// data-plane WORK runs). This is a TIER-0 plugin (bootstrap-critical, selected
// at boot — plugin-architecture.md): the core needs one to launch any other
// out-of-process plugin.
//
// Capability mapping:
//   rat://deployment-runtime/v1/launch    -> Launch
//   rat://deployment-runtime/v1/terminate -> Terminate
//   rat://deployment-runtime/v1/healthcheck -> Healthcheck
//
// SECURITY (reviews/04 I9 — minimum isolation profile): a deployment-runtime
// MUST honor the IsolationProfile (non-root, cap_drop ALL, no-new-privileges,
// read-only FS, blocked metadata egress). The profile is part of the LaunchSpec
// so it is contract, not convention — a runtime that ignores it fails conformance.
// This is the trust boundary the whole "install many 3rd-party plugins" bet leans
// on (reviews/01), so it is wire-level, not a deployment nicety.

